an male painters]]\n[[Category:21st-century German painters]]\n[[Category:Modern painters]]\n[[Category:German contemporary artists]]\n", "name_user": "G\u00fcnniX", "label": "safe", "comment": "http", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Richard_Schur"}
{"title_page": "Todd Woodcroft", "text_new": "{{Infobox college coach\n| name = Todd Woodcroft\t\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| current_title = [[Head coach]]\n| current_team = [[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|Vermont]]\n| current_conference = [[Hockey East]]\n| current_record = \n| contract = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|8|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| alma_mater = [[McGill University|McGill]] '95<br>[[University of Toronto]] '96\n| coach_years1 = 2000\u20132005\n| coach_team1 = [[Minnesota Wild]] (video coach)\n| coach_years2 = 2004\n| coach_team2 = [[Hockey Canada|Canada]] (video coach)\n| coach_years3 = 2005\u20132006\n| coach_team3 = [[Washington Capitals]] (video coach)\n| coach_years4 = 2006\n| coach_team4 = [[Belarus men's national ice hockey team|Belarus]] (assistant)\n| coach_years5 = 2006\u20132008\n| coach_team5 = Washington Capitals (scout)\n| coach_years6 = 2008\u20132009\n| coach_team6 = Minnesota Wild (scout)\n| coach_years7 = 2008\u20132009\n| coach_team7 = [[HC Dinamo Minsk]] (Asst. GM)\n| coach_years8 = 2009\u20132013\n| coach_team8 = [[Los Angeles Kings]] (scout)\n| coach_years9 = 2013\u20132016\n| coach_team9 = [[Calgary Flames]] (scout)\n| coach_years10 = 2013\u20132014\n| coach_team10 = Belarus (assistant)\n| coach_years11 = 2014\u20132015\n| coach_team11 = [[Switzerland men's national ice hockey team|Switzerland]] (assistant)\n| coach_years12 = 2015\u20132016\n| coach_team12 = Belarus (assistant)\n| coach_years13 = 2016\u20132017\n| coach_team13 = [[Sweden men's national ice hockey team|Sweden]] (assistant)\n| coach_years14 = 2016\u20132020\n| coach_team14 = [[Winnipeg Jets]] (assistant)\n| coach_years15 = 2020\u2013present\n| coach_team15 = [[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|Vermont]]\n| overall_record = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n| bowl_record = \n| tournament_record = \n| championships = \n| awards = Gold Medal, [[2004 IIHF World Championship]] (Canada)<br>[[2012 Stanley Cup Finals|2012]] Stanley Cup (Los Angeles Kings)<br>Gold Medal, [[2017 IIHF World Championship]] (Sweden)\n| coaching_records = \n}}\n'''Todd Woodcroft''' (born August 15, 1972) is a [[Canadian]] [[ice hockey]] coach. He is the current head coach of the [[University of Vermont]] [[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|men's ice hockey]] team.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://uvmathletics.com/news/2020/4/15/mens-ice-hockey-todd-woodcroft-named-head-mens-hockey-coach-at-vermont.aspx|title=Todd Woodcroft Named Head Men\u2019s Hockey Coach at Vermont|website=University of Vermont Athletics}}</ref>\n\n==Coaching career==\nWoodcroft began coaching by running his own hockey school until joining the [[Minnesota Wild]] as a video coach in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.collegehockeynews.com/news/2020/04/15_NHL-Assistant-Woodcroft-Offered.php|title=NHL Assistant Woodcroft Offered Vermont Head Coach Job|website=College Hockey News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qctimes.com/sports/woodcroft-makes-wild-jump-to-nhl/article_ad38e7a0-71c8-5995-a913-c030cdbf38ac.html|title=Woodcroft makes Wild jump to NHL|first=Craig Cooper, QUAD-CITY TIMES \u2014|last=October 17, 2000|website=The Quad-City Times}}</ref> During his work with the Wild, Woodcroft also served as a video coach for [[Canada men's national ice hockey team|Team Canada]] at the [[2004 IIHF World Championship]], helping the team win a Gold medal.<ref name=\"auto\">https://www.swehockey.se/globalassets/svenska-ishockeyforbundet/landslag/herr/tre-kronor/20162017/team-swedens-organization-and-team-management-season-20162017/todd_woodcroft.pdf</ref> From 2006 to 2009, he'd serve in scouting role with the [[Washington Capitals]] and Wild respectively, while also serving as an assistant coach for [[Belarus men's national ice hockey team|Belarus]] during the [[2006 IIHF World Championship]]. Woodcroft also served as the assistant general manager and director of player personnel for one season at [[HC Dinamo Minsk]]. \n\nFrom 2009 to 2013, Woodcroft was a scout for the [[Los Angeles Kings]], and was part of the team's [[2012 Stanley Cup Finals|2012 Stanley Cup]]-winning squad. He'd join the [[Calgary Flames]] as the director of scouting, while simultaneously coaching for both Belarus and [[Switzerland men's national ice hockey team|Switzerland]] during international competition. In 2016, he'd join the [[Winnipeg Jets]] as an assistant coach under [[Paul Maurice]].<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/winnipeg-jets-todd-woodcroft-1.3711957</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhl.com/jets/team/hockeyoperations/todd-woodcroft|title=Hockey Operations - Todd Woodcroft|website=Winnipeg Jets}}</ref> Woodcroft would also be on staff for [[Sweden men's national ice hockey team|Sweden]]'s [[2017 IIHF World Championship]] Gold medal performance, and during the [[2016 World Cup of Hockey]].<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nOn April 15, 2020 Woodcroft was named the fifth head coach in University of Vermont history, replacing [[Kevin Sneddon]].<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/sports/college/vermont/2020/04/15/uvm-tabs-nhl-assistant-coach-todd-woodcroft-lead-mens-hockey-program/5139888002/|title=UVM tabs NHL assistant coach Todd Woodcroft to lead men's hockey program|first=Alex|last=Abrami|website=Burlington Free Press}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWoodcroft comes from a hockey family. His older brother [[Craig Woodcroft|Craig]] is the head coach at Dinamo Minsk, while younger brother [[Jay Woodcroft|Jay]] is currently the head coach of the [[AHL]]'s [[Bakersfield Condors]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eliteprospects.com/staff/16401/craig-woodcroft|title=Elite Prospects - Craig Woodcroft Team Staff Profile|website=www.eliteprospects.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakersfieldcondors.com/news/getting-to-know-jay-woodcroft/|title=BakersfieldCondors.com &#124; GETTING TO KNOW: JAY WOODCROFT}}</ref> Two of his uncles were part of the \"Flying Fathers,\" a traveling hockey team of ordained Catholic priests.<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/sports-content/hockey/opinion/2014/01/the-woodcrofts-a-unique-hockey-day-in-canada-family.html</ref>\n\n==Head coaching record==\n{{CBB Yearly Record Start\n|type=coach\n|conference=\n|postseason=\n|poll=no\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Subhead\n|name=[[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|Vermont]]\n|startyear=2020\n|conference=[[Hockey East]]\n|endyear=\n|}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship = \n | season       = [[2020\u201321 NCAA Division I men's ice hockey season|2020\u201321]]\n | name         = [[2020\u201321 Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey season|Vermont]]\n | overall      = 0\u20130\u20130\n | conference   = 0\u20130\u20130\n | confstanding = \n | postseason   = \n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Subtotal\n | name       = Vermont\n | overall    = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n | confrecord = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record End\n|overall      = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n|confrecord   = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{hockeydb|197318}}\n*[https://www.eliteprospects.com/staff/1829/todd-woodcroft Todd Woodcroft at EliteProspects]\n\n{{Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey navbox}}\n{{Hockey East men's coach navbox}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Woodcroft, Todd}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey coaches]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey people from Ontario]]\n[[Category:McGill University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Toronto alumni]]\n[[Category:Winnipeg Jets coaches]]\n[[Category:Minnesota Wild scouts]]\n[[Category:Washington Capitals scouts]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles Kings scouts]]\n[[Category:Calgary Flames scouts]]\n[[Category:Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey coaches]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox college coach\n| name = Todd Woodcroft\t\n| image = \n| alt = \n| caption = \n| current_title = [[Head coach]]\n| current_team = [[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|Vermont]]\n| current_conference = [[Hockey East]]\n| current_record = \n| contract = \n| birth_date = {{birth date and age|1972|8|15}}\n| birth_place = [[Toronto]], [[Ontario]]\n| death_date = \n| death_place = \n| alma_mater = [[McGill University|McGill]] '95<br>[[University of Toronto]] '96\n| coach_years1 = 2000\u20132005\n| coach_team1 = [[Minnesota Wild]] (video coach)\n| coach_years2 = 2004\n| coach_team2 = [[Hockey Canada|Canada]] (video coach)\n| coach_years3 = 2005\u20132006\n| coach_team3 = [[Washington Capitals]] (video coach)\n| coach_years4 = 2006\n| coach_team4 = [[Belarus men's national ice hockey team|Belarus]] (assistant)\n| coach_years5 = 2006\u20132008\n| coach_team5 = Washington Capitals (scout)\n| coach_years6 = 2008\u20132009\n| coach_team6 = Minnesota Wild (scout)\n| coach_years7 = 2008\u20132009\n| coach_team7 = [[HC Dinamo Minsk]] (Asst. GM)\n| coach_years8 = 2009\u20132013\n| coach_team8 = [[Los Angeles Kings]] (scout)\n| coach_years9 = 2013\u20132016\n| coach_team9 = [[Calgary Flames]] (scout)\n| coach_years10 = 2013\u20132014\n| coach_team10 = Belarus (assistant)\n| coach_years11 = 2014\u20132015\n| coach_team11 = [[Switzerland men's national ice hockey team|Switzerland]] (assistant)\n| coach_years12 = 2015\u20132016\n| coach_team12 = Belarus (assistant)\n| coach_years13 = 2016\u20132017\n| coach_team13 = [[Sweden men's national ice hockey team|Sweden]] (assistant)\n| coach_years14 = 2016\u20132020\n| coach_team14 = [[Winnipeg Jets]] (assistant)\n| coach_years15 = 2020\u2013present\n| coach_team15 = [[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|Vermont]]\n| overall_record = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n| bowl_record = \n| tournament_record = \n| championships = \n| awards = Gold Medal, [[2004 IIHF World Championship]] (Canada)<br>[[2012 Stanley Cup Finals|2012]] Stanley Cup (Los Angeles Kings)<br>Gold Medal, [[2017 IIHF World Championship]] (Sweden)\n| coaching_records = \n}}\n'''Todd Woodcroft''' (born August 15, 1972) is an [[Canadian]] [[ice hockey]] coach. He is the current head coach of the [[University of Vermont]] [[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|men's ice hockey]] team.<ref name=\"auto1\">{{Cite web|url=https://uvmathletics.com/news/2020/4/15/mens-ice-hockey-todd-woodcroft-named-head-mens-hockey-coach-at-vermont.aspx|title=Todd Woodcroft Named Head Men\u2019s Hockey Coach at Vermont|website=University of Vermont Athletics}}</ref>\n\n==Coaching career==\nWoodcroft began coaching by running his own hockey school until joining the [[Minnesota Wild]] as a video coach in 2000.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.collegehockeynews.com/news/2020/04/15_NHL-Assistant-Woodcroft-Offered.php|title=NHL Assistant Woodcroft Offered Vermont Head Coach Job|website=College Hockey News}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://qctimes.com/sports/woodcroft-makes-wild-jump-to-nhl/article_ad38e7a0-71c8-5995-a913-c030cdbf38ac.html|title=Woodcroft makes Wild jump to NHL|first=Craig Cooper, QUAD-CITY TIMES \u2014|last=October 17, 2000|website=The Quad-City Times}}</ref> During his work with the Wild, Woodcroft also served as a video coach for [[Canada men's national ice hockey team|Team Canada]] at the [[2004 IIHF World Championship]], helping the team win a Gold medal.<ref name=\"auto\">https://www.swehockey.se/globalassets/svenska-ishockeyforbundet/landslag/herr/tre-kronor/20162017/team-swedens-organization-and-team-management-season-20162017/todd_woodcroft.pdf</ref> From 2006 to 2009, he'd serve in scouting role with the [[Washington Capitals]] and Wild respectively, while also serving as an assistant coach for [[Belarus men's national ice hockey team|Belarus]] during the [[2006 IIHF World Championship]]. Woodcroft also served as the assistant general manager and director of player personnel for one season at [[HC Dinamo Minsk]]. \n\nFrom 2009 to 2013, Woodcroft was a scout for the [[Los Angeles Kings]], and was part of the team's [[2012 Stanley Cup Finals|2012 Stanley Cup]]-winning squad. He'd join the [[Calgary Flames]] as the director of scouting, while simultaneously coaching for both Belarus and [[Switzerland men's national ice hockey team|Switzerland]] during international competition. In 2016, he'd join the [[Winnipeg Jets]] as an assistant coach under [[Paul Maurice]].<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/news/canada/manitoba/winnipeg-jets-todd-woodcroft-1.3711957</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.nhl.com/jets/team/hockeyoperations/todd-woodcroft|title=Hockey Operations - Todd Woodcroft|website=Winnipeg Jets}}</ref> Woodcroft would also be on staff for [[Sweden men's national ice hockey team|Sweden]]'s [[2017 IIHF World Championship]] Gold medal performance, and during the [[2016 World Cup of Hockey]].<ref name=\"auto\"/>\n\nOn April 15, 2020 Woodcroft was named the fifth head coach in University of Vermont history, replacing [[Kevin Sneddon]].<ref name=\"auto1\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.burlingtonfreepress.com/story/sports/college/vermont/2020/04/15/uvm-tabs-nhl-assistant-coach-todd-woodcroft-lead-mens-hockey-program/5139888002/|title=UVM tabs NHL assistant coach Todd Woodcroft to lead men's hockey program|first=Alex|last=Abrami|website=Burlington Free Press}}</ref>\n\n==Personal life==\nWoodcroft comes from a hockey family. His older brother [[Craig Woodcroft|Craig]] is the head coach at Dinamo Minsk, while younger brother [[Jay Woodcroft|Jay]] is currently the head coach of the [[AHL]]'s [[Bakersfield Condors]].<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.eliteprospects.com/staff/16401/craig-woodcroft|title=Elite Prospects - Craig Woodcroft Team Staff Profile|website=www.eliteprospects.com}}</ref><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.bakersfieldcondors.com/news/getting-to-know-jay-woodcroft/|title=BakersfieldCondors.com &#124; GETTING TO KNOW: JAY WOODCROFT}}</ref> Two of his uncles were part of the \"Flying Fathers,\" a traveling hockey team of ordained Catholic priests.<ref>https://www.cbc.ca/sports-content/hockey/opinion/2014/01/the-woodcrofts-a-unique-hockey-day-in-canada-family.html</ref>\n\n==Head coaching record==\n{{CBB Yearly Record Start\n|type=coach\n|conference=\n|postseason=\n|poll=no\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Subhead\n|name=[[Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey|Vermont]]\n|startyear=2020\n|conference=[[Hockey East]]\n|endyear=\n|}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Entry\n | championship = \n | season       = [[2020\u201321 NCAA Division I men's ice hockey season|2020\u201321]]\n | name         = [[2020\u201321 Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey season|Vermont]]\n | overall      = 0\u20130\u20130\n | conference   = 0\u20130\u20130\n | confstanding = \n | postseason   = \n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record Subtotal\n | name       = Vermont\n | overall    = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n | confrecord = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n}}\n{{CBB Yearly Record End\n|overall      = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n|confrecord   = 0\u20130\u20130 ({{winpct|0|0|0}})\n}}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n*{{hockeydb|197318}}\n*[https://www.eliteprospects.com/staff/1829/todd-woodcroft Todd Woodcroft at EliteProspects]\n\n{{Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey navbox}}\n{{Hockey East men's coach navbox}}\n\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Woodcroft, Todd}}\n[[Category:1972 births]]\n[[Category:Living people]]\n[[Category:Canadian ice hockey coaches]]\n[[Category:Ice hockey people from Ontario]]\n[[Category:McGill University alumni]]\n[[Category:University of Toronto alumni]]\n[[Category:Winnipeg Jets coaches]]\n[[Category:Minnesota Wild scouts]]\n[[Category:Washington Capitals scouts]]\n[[Category:Los Angeles Kings scouts]]\n[[Category:Calgary Flames scouts]]\n[[Category:Vermont Catamounts men's ice hockey coaches]]\n", "name_user": "Orenburg1", "label": "safe", "comment": "sp", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Todd_Woodcroft"}
